'''''Zucker''''' (Sugar) is the sixth studio album by German [[Pop music|pop]] duo [[Rosenstolz]]. Released in 1999 by [[Polydor Records]], it was the first Rosenstolz album to enter the top 10 of the [[GfK Entertainment|German albums chart]].

==Background==
Following its release in April 1999, ''Zucker'' went straight to No.&nbsp;2 in the German albums chart.<ref>[http://musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/artist/Rosenstolz/22195/?type=longplay "Chartverfolgung / Rosenstolz / Longplay"] (in German). musicline.de. PHONONET GmbH. Retrieved 3 May 2014.</ref> In an interview, singer [[AnNa&nbsp;R.]] of Rosenstolz described the album as being more personal than earlier Rosenstolz albums. She further stated that the album was more mature in terms of the lyrics and the themes dealt with, attributing this to the fact that the band members were getting older.<ref name="Gegen">[http://www.gegenpol.net/archiv/1999/139-04/3517-rosenstolz-mit-qzuckerq-lacht-das-leben "Rosenstolz - Mit "Zucker" lacht das Leben"] (in German). ''GEGENPOL''. April 1999.</ref>

"Perlentaucher" and "Fütter deine Angst", two songs from ''Zucker'', reached No.&nbsp;40 and No.&nbsp;52, respectively, in the [[GfK Entertainment|German singles chart]].<ref>[http://www.officialcharts.de/song.asp?artist=Rosenstolz&title=Perlentaucher&cat=s&country=de "Single &ndash; Rosenstolz, Perlentaucher"] (in German). charts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]]. Retrieved 13 October 2014.</ref><ref>[http://www.officialcharts.de/song.asp?artist=Rosenstolz&title=F%FCtter+deine+Angst+%2F+Ja%2C+ich+will&cat=s&country=de "Single &ndash; Rosenstolz, Fütter deine Angst / Ja, ich will"] (in German). charts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]]. Retrieved 13 October 2014.</ref> "Fütter deine Angst" was part of a double single with "Ja, ich will", and the latter together with "Zucker III" were included in a re-release of ''Zucker'' as bonus songs.<ref>[http://www.officialcharts.de/album.asp?artist=Rosenstolz&title=Zucker&cat=a&country=de "Album &ndash; Rosenstolz, Zucker"] (in German). charts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]]. Retrieved 13 October 2014.</ref> "Ja, ich will" was a collaboration with German comedian [[Hella von Sinnen]], calling for the introduction of [[same-sex marriage]].<ref>[http://www.queer.de/detail.php?article_id=18152 "Das Ende von Rosenstolz"] (in German). ''queer.de''. 19 December 2012.</ref>

==Concert tour and live album==
Songs from ''Zucker'' were introduced in the Rosenstolz concert tour which took place in Germany and Switzerland during May and June 1999.<ref name="Gegen" /> These songs included "Zucker II", "Ein anderes Gefühl von Schmerz", "Fütter deine Angst" and "Schieß mich jetzt ab".<ref>CD insert notes (1999) (in German). ''Zuckerschlampen:live''. Rosenstolz. Universal Music Group. 547 982-2.</ref> During the tour, Rosenstolz's first [[live album]] was recorded.<ref>[http://www.rosenstolz.de/magazin/bio-rosenstolz "Rosenstolz Magazin - 20 Jahre Rosenstolz"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703234957/http://www.rosenstolz.de/magazin/bio-rosenstolz |date=July 3, 2014 }} (in German). Official Rosenstolz website. Retrieved 5 October 2014.</ref> Titled ''Zuckerschlampen:live'', the album was released in September 1999 by Polydor Records and reached No.&nbsp;5 in the German albums chart.<ref>[http://www.officialcharts.de/album.asp?artist=Rosenstolz&title=Zuckerschlampen+Live&cat=a&country=de "Album &ndash; Rosenstolz, Zuckerschlampen Live"] (in German). charts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]]. Retrieved 5 October 2014.</ref>

